				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To the individual who claims the PoD is lvl 75 because a guide told him so...<BR>
<BR>
#1. Because lvl 40s and 50s can cast magic on him, this it untrue. Verant themselves admits that their is a +6 lvl cap on being nearly impervious to magic (i.e., a 30 won't be able to affect a lvl 40 with magic, but could a 36, just with high resists).<BR>
<BR>
#2. Guides NEVER reveal that type of information. GMs and Guides will never give out the specifics on NPCs or anything else in game. They barely tell you anything that is actually relevant and important let alone NPC details. All they did was up the HPs of various NPCs to make them more difficult to kill.<BR>
<BR>
On a side note, I have to agree with the many posts that considering the extreme difficulty of the PoD relative to his loot... these items (the Staff and Robe of Discord) really suck, imo. Better stuff drops off easy-to-kill mid-20s to early-30s mobs. The only thing worth anything (if that's your interest) is the status of owning such an item, but the ability for other ppl to obtain the items (either as gifts, allowed to loot, etc.), so it's not guaranteed the holder is responsible in anyway for the death. SOOO... IMO, this has practically no value whatsoever. You can do better, Verant, so please try.
				</font>
			</td>

