			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It is a well known fact that the computer cheats in almost if not all computer games. Everquest is no different.<BR>
<BR>
The highest amount of HP ANYTHING in the game has is 32,000. I would assume that the PoD and dragons have this amount. The highest level that anything in the game can be due to the restrictions put on players (befor expansion) is 56. I believe it when people say the PoD is level 50. NPC levels are not the same as player levels. I thought this was obvious but with the way some of you are talking I guess it is not.<BR>
A level 50 NPC can sure as well seem like a level 75 because that is probably what level a PLAYER would need to be to be equal in skill.<BR>
<BR>
This is why as a caster goes up in level, there pet cons lower and lower. The pet is run off of an NPC script and that is why it is made lower and lower. If you had a pet that conned even to a level 50. It would come real close to solo'ing the PoD. Pets are made lower than caster levels due to the fact that they are trying to make it so you have a pet about equivelent to the casters level and abilities.<BR>
<BR>
ANYWAY... The PoD is, again I will say, a NPC and has no or little restrictions to use of spells and equipement. Also, the PoD will never fizzle! Inturupting a level 50 NPC is not somthing you should rely on since it will probably not happen.<BR>
<BR>
NPC's dont have a set class. They have what they are told to have based on what NPC they are. So if the GM's wanted to be mean they could throw out a NPC with the use of ALL SPELLS in the game. Who knows, the PoD could be set up that way and just doesnt have the reason to use some spells.<BR>
It wouldn't supprize me in the least if the PoD harm touched somone some day and then used Lay of Hands on himself right after<BR>
<BR>
Umm... Lost my train of though...<BR>
Not trying to sound like a know it all or like a jerk or anything, just sharing the knowledge.
				</font>
			</td>

